# Ingredients

1 Cup Milk, warm
1 tsp Sugar, white, granulated
2 tsp Yeast, active, dry
3 ounces Butter, melted
3 Cups Flour, white, all-purpose or bread
4 Egg Yolks
1/4 tsp Salt[^1]

# Method


## 0. Yeast
1. Warm 1 cup Milk
1. Pour half cup back into measuring cup, pour other half into bowl.
1. Stir in 1 tsp Sugar.
1. Stir in 2 tsp Yeast. You should get a yeasty aroma right away.
1. Let bloom 15 minutes.

## 1. Dough

Use a kitchen stand mixer with a dough hook attachment, on low:

1. 4 Egg Yolks
1. 1/3 Cup Sugar
1. 1 Tbsp Vanilla
1. 3oz Butter, melted
1. 1/4 tsp Salt[^1]
1. Rest of the warm milk
1. 3 Cups Flour, a few tablespoons at a time until you have some bulk. 

Dough should be quite soft and yellow.

## 2. Rolls



## 3. Glaze, Frosting or Syrup

### Glaze

1/2 Cup Powdered Sugar
1 Tbsp Milk
1 tsp Orange or Lemon Juice

### Frosting

Add first three ingredients into a bowl in this order. Then mix with a fork. Add Vanilla last to ensure that everything is incorporated.

1 Tbsp Butter, room temperature
1 Cup Powedered Sugar
1 Tbsp Heavy Cream
1 tsp Vanilla


[^1]: Omit Salt if using Salted Butter
